						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Espozo wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">Sik wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> (especially given how overused pixelart is these days, especially pixelart that tries to look NES-like).</div><br />I think the main reason &quot;NES style&quot; pixel art is the most common is because it takes the least amount of effort to draw. Compared to SNES pixel art, there is much less to draw (smaller sprites, less animation for each sprite) and there are much less colors to use, both for each tile and total. After about making 3 frames of animation on an SNES sprite I'm making, I already want to pull my hair out.</div><br /><br />You can draw out a character using an animated outline and flat colors, and fill it out with shading.</div>

